+{\footnote index:00006}
K{\footnote ;What\'B4s a THL-File ?;Pictures;File formats;Hints;Multimedia files;THL files;THR files;}
{\f5\fs48\cf2\li120\ri250\sb40\sa40\b\ql THL-Files}\par\pard
{\f0\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60\brdrt}\par\pard
{\f2\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60\ql THL-Files are binary files which contain text, pictures and multimediadata. They are designed for the use with the "{\uldb reader}{\v Der_THL_Reader}" of this software, but they are not suitable for ordinary texteditors. In general the creation of THL-Files consists of three main steps:}\par\pard
{\f0\cf1\li180\ri250\sa-260\fs16\fi0}\par\pard
{\f0\brdrth\box\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60\f4 \'B7\f0\brdrth\box\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60\ql\li540\fi-360\tx540\tab Enter hints, include pictures, ... with the THL-Editor}\par\pard
{\f0\brdrth\box\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60\f4 \'B7\f0\brdrth\box\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60\ql\li540\fi-360\tx540\tab Eventually save your data as THR-File (highly recommened). A THR-File saves your data without compiling them.\line \b CAUTION:\b0  THL-File can not be edited with the THL-Editor anymore. Always keep a copy of your THR-File at a save place.}\par\pard
{\f0\brdrth\box\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60\f4 \'B7\f0\brdrth\box\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60\ql\li540\fi-360\tx540\tab Compile the editor data into a THL-File.}\par\pard
{\f0\fs24\cf1\li180\ri250\sb60\sa20\b\ql }\par\pard
{\f0\fs24\cf1\li180\ri250\sb60\sa20\b\ql The structure of THR/THL-Files:}\par\pard
{\f2\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60\ql Ordinary a hint collection is divided into deveral topics. These topic either contain subtopics or hints. Hints and topics can not be combined at one level.\line There are different hint types:}\par\pard
{\f0\cf1\li180\ri250\sa-260\fs16\fi0}\par\pard
{\f0\brdrth\box\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60\f4 \'B7\f0\brdrth\box\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60\ql\li540\fi-360\tx540\tab Text ( single or multiple lines )}\par\pard
{\f0\brdrth\box\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60\f4 \'B7\f0\brdrth\box\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60\ql\li540\fi-360\tx540\tab Pictures, supported file formats: Bitmap, JPeg, PCX, Targa\line Special features: You may define parts of pictures and attach independent descriptions.}\par\pard
{\f0\brdrth\box\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60\f4 \'B7\f0\brdrth\box\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60\ql\li540\fi-360\tx540\tab Multimedia-Files, suported formats: WAV, AVI, MIDI, MOV. Some additional formats are supported, but the use is not recommened due to compability reasons.}\par\pard
{\f2\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60\ql Two examples:\line Valid structure:\line Topic1 ---> Hints 1..3\line Topic2 ---> Subtopic1, Subtopic2\line Topic3 ---> Picture, Hints 1..6\line \line Invalid structure:\line Topic1 ---> Hints 1..3\line Topic2 ---> Subtopic1, Hints1..9 ( ERROR )\line ...}\par\pard
{\f0\cf1\li180\ri250\sa-260\fs16\fi0}\par\pard
