{\f0\cf1\li180\ri250\sa-260\fs16\fi0}\par\pard
{\f0\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60 1 \li540\fi-360\tx540\tab\ql This tree view shows your current project. Hints are marked with the prefix HINT, pictures are marked with PIC, and multimedia files are marked with MM. You always will see the starting characters of a title. The root directory contains topics only. Topics either contain subtopics or hints, pictures, or multimedia files. When adding new entries the currently selected entry becomes owner of the new entry. According to your avaible selections the buttons 2-5 become enabled or disabled.}\par\pard
{\f0\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60 2 \li540\fi-360\tx540\tab\ql Pressing this button open a window for adding a new topic to your project.}\par\pard
{\f0\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60 3 \li540\fi-360\tx540\tab\ql Here you can add a new hint to your project.}\par\pard
{\f0\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60 4 \li540\fi-360\tx540\tab\ql This button opens the picture editor which is used to add new picture links or area definitions to your project.}\par\pard
{\f0\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60 5 \li540\fi-360\tx540\tab\ql Pressing button no 5 open a window for adding multimedia files to your project. Please note that normally video files are rather large and therefore the size of the THL file will increase significantly. Although the multimedia support of THE HINT LIBRARY only depends on the capabilites of your system, unusual files formats may not be supported by different systems.}\par\pard
{\f0\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60 6 \li540\fi-360\tx540\tab\ql Edit the selected entry. The software will select the appropriate window for the entry. It is not possible to change type of an entry.}\par\pard
{\f0\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60 7 \li540\fi-360\tx540\tab\ql Delete the currently selected entry. Please note that you even delete all children of this entry. Use this function carefully !}\par\pard
{\f0\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60 8 \li540\fi-360\tx540\tab\ql This buttons moves the currently selected item within its level upwards. Associated children will be moved either.}\par\pard
{\f0\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60 9 \li540\fi-360\tx540\tab\ql Moving downwards...}\par\pard
{\f0\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60 10 \li540\fi-360\tx540\tab\ql Enter a title for your document here. This is not a file name, but a title which appears as header in the {\uldb Reader}{\v Der_THL_Reader}. This entry is nessesary for successfull compilation.}\par\pard
{\f0\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60 11 \li540\fi-360\tx540\tab\ql With this button you can choose a font which will be used with the Reader to display the title of your document. Please note that the use non standard fonts may cause unwanted  effects on computer system which do not have the fonts installed.}\par\pard
{\f0\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60 12 \li540\fi-360\tx540\tab\ql Use this window to enter copyright notice, e.g. \i Written 1996 by Harry Hummel\i0 . This field must be filled in for proper compilation.}\par\pard
{\f0\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60 13 \li540\fi-360\tx540\tab\ql Here you can enter additional information about your project.}\par\pard
{\f0\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60 14 \li540\fi-360\tx540\tab\ql This button opens a Save File-Dialog for saving your project as THR file. You need this THR file for later changes. It is highly recommend to save THR files of each important development state of your project.}\par\pard
{\f0\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60 15 \li540\fi-360\tx540\tab\ql This button compiles your project into a THL file.}\par\pard
{\f0\fs20\cf1\li180\ri250\sb20\sa60 16 \li540\fi-360\tx540\tab\ql Press this button to exit THL Editor. Always save your project before leaving the editor.}\par\pard
